    "The last example is a system dynamics model of systems thinking and team performance that builds on a confirmatory factor analysis (CFA) and exploratory factor analysis (EFA) of the Systems Thinking Scale Revised (Davis and Stroink, 2016) using SEM.",
    "The \"Limits to Growth\" model (Figure 6) has one latent state variable representing the population, two latent flows, three constants, and three latent auxiliary variables as shown in the figure below.",
    "Translating this into a general model requires adding an additional static \"auxiliary\" variable y 9 to facilitate interactions between the dynamic variable x 1 and static variables.",
    "We also take advantage of the restriction in system dynamics that static variables cannot form feedback loops, which allows us to define constants by setting the exponent to zero and coefficient to the value of the constant, i.e., y i = c implies β 2,i,i = c and γ 2,i,i = 0.",
    "Table 3 below provides the specification for specific terms."
